Palmer expects to be fined by the British Horseracing Authority (BHA) for the rule breach during Champions Day. "It was an honest and open challenge over the length of time," he said. "It was a challenge within our legal framework within the league at a time that we were trying to recover from the incident. I was just surprised it happened. I don't expect the BHA, and any club that holds any weight in the Championship, to be able to put our head down in the way that they should have.

"The BHA and the FA and our leadership should be accountable for the mistakes that they've made, not those involved in the matter, and our players should have a clear explanation for what they committed. This was an honest and responsible response from the team. It took their action into account, and the BHA, and the leadership should have clear explanations from referees."

The game played on the first Sunday of every other weekend;
